The testSkewedRack3 test checks if a block has the redundancy needed for erasure coding after creating a file. The test does this check 10 times, each time with a different test file. During the iteration, the test checks whether the blocks are replicated 9 times - on 9 different hosts.

The issue seems to be that the check is done without a delay or a retry:
{code:java}
      DFSTestUtil.writeFile(dfs, path, contents);
      BlockLocation[] blocks =
          dfs.getFileBlockLocations(path, 0, Long.MAX_VALUE);
      assertEquals(ecPolicy.getNumDataUnits() + ecPolicy.getNumParityUnits(),
          blocks[0].getHosts().length);
{code}

Adding a retry with 10ms delay between the {{writeFile}} and {{getFileBlockLocations}} eliminates the issue and during my tests, the maximum number of retries was 3, so that means after ~30ms delay the issue is gone.
A solution to eliminate this issue could be to add a retry with a 50ms delay, with a low maximal number of retries. 
If such a delay cannot be accepted during this test, then further debugging, maybe optimization needed.
